From b626ddbe155feb25486ac170bc267a05ece34cb3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:22:25 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] lib: translate earlycpio to Rust (linux-rs TU 23)

Early-boot uncompressed cpio member finder: hex-field header parser
(14 fields, 6-char magic + 8-char rest) with buffer-overrun bounds
checks on the computed dptr/nptr pointers, matching the C's goto quit
early-exits as plain returns (no cleanup happens at quit -- bare
early-exit). Real finding: #[export] requires the EXACT bindgen struct
type (kernel::bindings::cpio_data), not a locally-defined #[repr(C)]
lookalike -- even an identical-layout struct is a different Rust type
to the compiler; aliased via 'use bindings::cpio_data as CpioData'
instead. Extended the pr_debug shim pattern from TU 22 to pr_warn
(rust/helpers/print.c) for the MAX_CPIO_FILE_NAME-exceeded warning.

No dedicated KUnit suite covers find_cpio_data and no tier-2.5 diff
harness was built for it this pass (would need a hex-cpio-format fuzz
generator -- real follow-up work, not done here to keep moving through
the queue). Validated at tiers 1-4: builds, #[export] prototype-checked
against <linux/earlycpio.h>, symbol confirmed in System.map, full
regression boot green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
